Have you ever set out to do one thing but ended up with something completely different?
My study here was ‘stems and the textures that they have’. But I discovered something totally different.
I wanted a dark background to show them better and used my Copic airbrush. I’m not very good at using it and it didn’t blend well, I just kept adding blendable colours to try and smooth it out. Nope. It totally took away from my ‘stems’ so, I tried an experiment. 
I took a white charcoal pencil and sharpened it so that I had a little pile of dust. I then rubbed the white powder into my background and it looks like PASTELS. So not a complete fail. Still gotta work things out.
I will have to try this technique again. Mind that it needs to be charcoal(chalk), coloured pencil won’t blend the same way.
If you have a white charcoal pencil, try it to blend and let me know what you think.

Did you know that Hydrangeas are Allergy Safe Flowers?
🪻🌷🌻 🤧
Hydrangeas are unique because they have super sticky pollen. That makes it difficult for wind to blow the pollen around, making these flowers perfect for allergy sufferers.

Hydrangea just before it becomes a big ball of blooms.

Nerine Bowdenii

The story goes that the flowers drifted on the seas from South Africa, eventually washing up on the shores of the island of Guernsey. It was this ocean voyage that earned the flower its name: ‘Nerine’, in a reference to the 50 beautiful daughters of the sea-god Nereus. The flower is also known as the Guernsey Lily. It symbolizes that which is often left unsaid, thus bridging the gap between heart and mind.
Illustrated In Copic markers on Ohuhu sketchbook paper. I used no liner pens for this one because I wanted a very light and delicate feel. It’s been a challenge for me to not outline. I do however like the look.

I haven’t posted in a while. It’s been busy and while I have been drawing, I just haven’t had a chance to photograph the art. It’ll happen though 😉
I’m also getting disenchanted with Instagram. My last few posts were only shown to a handful of people. Instagram just doesn’t think they should show my posts, not even to people who follow me. I’m not sure why you wouldn’t show posts to people who signed up to see them. I myself only ever see the same dozen people in my timeline. I have to search people that I follow already just to see their posts. It’s making Instagram less fun. Anyhow, I’ve complained about Instagram many times and much too often so, it is what it is. 🤔🤷‍♀️
I’ll post when I’m in the mood and I hope you all understand and continue to support my love for drawing. 
Xoxo. I’m not going to leave Instagram, even if it doesn’t seem to be on my side. 🥰😘😍

So Fluffy. 
This one would need lots of brushing 😄
Two of my cats ( Squink and Gable) love being brushed. The just see the brush and come running. They also have the shortest and silkiest fur. 
Two others ( Boba and Dzikus) could take it or leave it. They are medium fluffy, actually Boba is pretty extra fluffy 😆 Anyway, They tolerate brushing and don’t necessarily run away but they aren’t excited like the other two. 
Now Kluski, HATES being brushed and she’s the one that needs it the most. She’s super fluffy and tends to get little matted bits. I have tried so many types of brushes, from glove brushes, ones with clippers built in  traditional brushes, claw brushes, soft bristles, all kinds. She just hates being brushed, it takes two of us to hold her down and that is IF I can catch her. 
If she sees the brush - she RUNS! 😂😻

Lotus Pod.
Did you know?

The lotus is a divine symbol in a number of religuous traditions. It represents the virtue of purity and non-attachement. 
Lotus pods are the seed head of the lotus flower. Don’t you think it kind of looks like the spouts of watering can? Dried versions can last years and are often used in flower arrangements.
I decided to use a black background to make the pod ‘pop’ on the page. Not a usual thing that I do but it was an interesting process.

You all know I love drawing flowers 🌸 
I’ve realized that the last while I’ve not been using a liner pen to outline. Im accustomed to outlining all my drawings but  lately I use just the pencil, I’m not sure how that happened 😆!
However, for flowers not outlining, certainly makes them softer and lighter. 
Anyway, I don’t have a go-to pencil, I grab whatever I have on my desk and sometimes they smudge more than I like. Tell me what you use.  I need one that I can lighten with my gum eraser but I don’t want the lead to smudge too much once I start painting in with markers , especially the lighter colours. Advice?
